================================================================================
SERVICENOW CMDB — CSA 2025 NOTES
================================================================================

1) WHAT IS CMDB?
----------------
• CMDB = Configuration Management Database.
• A collection of tables that store:
   - Configuration Items (CIs)
   - Relationships between CIs

• Used to understand infrastructure, services, and their dependencies.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2) CONFIGURATION ITEM (CI)
--------------------------
• A CI is any component managed by IT.
• Can be tangible or intangible.

Examples:
• Server
• Application
• Database instance
• Laptop / Desktop
• Business Service

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3) CMDB APPLICATION
-------------------
• ServiceNow provides an Out-of-the-Box CMDB application.
• Used to manage:
   - CI records
   - CI classes
   - CI relationships

IMPORTANT CSA NOTE:
• CMDB is managed using predefined tables and classes.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4) CI RECORD (IMPORTANT FIELDS)
--------------------------------
A CI record contains details such as:
• Name
• Asset Tag
• Manufacturer
• Asset (linked from Asset table)
• CI Class
• Company
• Serial Number / Model ID
• Assigned To
• Configuration attributes
   - Host name
   - OS
   - IP address
   - Domain

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5) RELATED ITEMS
-----------------
• Shows relationships with other CIs.
• Helps identify dependencies between CIs.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6) CI DASHBOARD VIEW
--------------------
• Provides health and quality metrics of a CI.
• Shows:
   - Completeness
   - Correctness
   - Compliance
   - Staleness
   - Related tasks (Incident, Change, Problem)

NOTE:
• Dashboard view is informational.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7) KEY CMDB TABLES (EXAM-CRITICAL)
----------------------------------
1. cmdb_ci
   - Base Configuration Item table.

2. cmdb_ci_<class>
   - Extended CI tables.
   - Examples:
     • cmdb_ci_server
     • cmdb_ci_application
     • cmdb_ci_computer

3. cmdb_rel_ci
   - Stores CI relationships.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8) CMDB CLASS HIERARCHY
-----------------------
• CMDB uses table inheritance.
• CI classes extend parent CI tables.
• Organized hierarchically.

Example:
• cmdb_ci
   → cmdb_ci_hardware
      → cmdb_ci_computer
   → cmdb_ci_application
      → cmdb_ci_app_server

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9) CI CLASS MANAGER
-------------------
• Displays all CI classes in a hierarchical tree.
• Used to:
   - View
   - Modify
   - Extend CI classes

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
10) CI RELATIONSHIPS
--------------------
• Define how CIs are connected.

Common relationship types:
• Depends on
• Used by
• Hosted on

• Stored in **cmdb_rel_ci** table.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11) CI DEPENDENCY VIEW (VERY IMPORTANT)
---------------------------------------
• Graphical view of CI relationships.
• Shows:
   - Upstream dependencies
   - Downstream dependencies
   - Impacted CIs

Used for:
• Impact analysis
• Root cause analysis

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
12) USAGE OF CMDB IN ITSM
-------------------------
• CIs are linked to:
   - Incident
   - Problem
   - Change
   - Request

Benefits:
• Faster issue resolution
• Better impact analysis
• Accurate reporting
• Auto-assignment possibilities

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
13) CSA EXAM TAKEAWAYS
----------------------
• CMDB stores CIs and their relationships.
• CI can be hardware, software, or service.
• cmdb_ci is the base CI table.
• CI classes extend parent CI tables.
• Relationships are stored in cmdb_rel_ci.
• Dependency View shows CI impact graphically.
• CMDB is heavily used in Incident, Problem, Change.

================================================================================
END OF CMDB — CSA 2025
